<I c="LootActions" i="action" m="interactions.utils.loot" n="loot_EP20Festival_PlumbirdFacts" s="462785">
  <L n="loot_actions">
    <V t="notification_and_dialog">
      <U n="notification_and_dialog">
        <V n="dialog" t="notification">
          <U n="notification">
            <L n="dialog_options">
              <E>DISABLE_CLOSE_BUTTON</E>
            </L>
            <V n="icon" t="enabled">
              <V n="enabled" t="resource_key">
                <U n="resource_key">
                  <T n="key" p="InEP20\UI\Icons\Notifications\notification_Cryptid.png">2f7d0004:00000000:7f801308f6e48e4e</T>
                </U>
              </V>
            </V>
            <V n="secondary_icon" t="enabled">
              <V n="enabled" t="participant">
                <U n="participant">
                  <L n="participant_type">
                    <E>TargetSim</E>
                  </L>
                </U>
              </V>
            </V>
            <V n="text" t="variation">
              <U n="variation">
                <L n="variations">
                  <T>0x25AC5DCC<!--String: "The Peculiar Plumbird mainly sticks to that nest of hers in Crystal Valley. I'll see her sometimes in the Wanderwood Wilds neighborhood, though. I don't know if she's shy or what. I know some other Sims told me once that all the other big Plumbirds disappeared over time so otherwise it's just those small ones you see over by the Hothead Rock Geyser or, well, the Peculiar one."--></T>
                  <T>0xFAEF1987<!--String: "I heard that once while Sims were out around a campfire at Camp Gibbi Gibbi way after dark, this terrifying giant bird swooped in and stole their marshmallows! They were absolutely terrified apparently. Sounds like that weird bird might be a bit scary, too. I'd watch your back around it."--></T>
                  <T>0x8674C9FA<!--String: "A lot of elders who were here before said that the size of Plumbirds changed over time and that they started avoiding Sims, especially around when the jellyfish started showing up in the Electric Lagoon."--></T>
                  <T>0x98D9D4E3<!--String: "Apparently, back when Gibbi Point was completely overtaken with lush plants just like Wanderwood Wilds is, there were so many Plumbirds that they were basically running the place. But that big one, that one's different. Some child Sims really love it, I wonder why?"--></T>
                  <T>0x71D05408<!--String: "The Peculiar Plumbird, that giant one over in Crystal Valley, seems freaky at first but I honestly think it just wants friends. I think it has trouble trusting other Sims and feels like maybe some of us don't make an effort to learn about Gibbi Point history. "--></T>
                </L>
              </U>
            </V>
          </U>
        </V>
      </U>
    </V>
  </L>
</I>